<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-74-0544 </DOCNO><TEXT>The purpose of this paper is to acquaint the reader with the various typesof financing that are available to the coal industry and the types oflenders that provide funds to the same. Additionally, the paper willcover the risks of lending to the coal business, the banks' credit criteriafor coal company loans and examples of financing structures along withthe collateral requirements for these transactions. The central thesisin all mineral lending, whether it be coal or oil and gas, or any othermining or mineral transaction, is that each transaction is unique andwill have different needs and different risks. As a result, the industryand the players must be well understood by the lender. Underlying thisthesis is the requirement that there must be good economic incentivesfor a transaction in order for it to be financed.</TEXT></DOC>